# DDAD — Document-Driven AI Development

This project follows DDAD. Documents in `ddad/docs/` are the source of truth; code implements what they specify.

Before writing code:
- Read `ddad/docs/00-overview.md`, `ddad/docs/01-requirements.md`, and `ddad/docs/02-architecture.md`.
- Check `ddad/docs/decisions/` for prior ADRs that constrain your approach. Don't contradict an accepted ADR without writing a new one that supersedes it.

While implementing:
- Update `ddad/docs/03-tasks.md` as task status changes.
- Write a new ADR in `ddad/docs/decisions/` for any decision that would be expensive to reverse.
- If a document is outdated or wrong, fix it in the same change instead of letting code and docs drift.

Do not implement features with no corresponding requirement in `ddad/docs/01-requirements.md` — flag the gap instead of silently expanding scope.

See AGENTS.md for the full workflow.
